hw07

Interface GTUIterator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GTUSet.GTUSetIterator

    public interface GTUIterator<T>
    This interface is the basis of an iterator that can be implemented for any generic container. This has all the necessary methods for an iterator.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int position
      Index-wise location of the iterator.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T current()
      Returns the value of the current element and does not move the iterator.
      int getPosition()
      Getter for position field.
      boolean hasNext()
      Returns a boolean value depending on the existence of a value at the next index of iterator.
      boolean hasPrevious()
      Returns a boolean value depending on the existence of a value at the previous index of iterator.
      T next()
      Returns the value of the next element if it exists and pushes iterator to the next address.
      T previous()
      Returns the value of the previous element if it exists and pushes iterator to the previous address.
